                    <div class="byline-date">
                        <a href="http://bikehugger.com/2007/12/should-seattle-license-cyclist.html#comment-5101"><abbr class="published" title="Permalink to this comment">December 27, 2007 &#183; 10:48 AM</abbr></a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="asset-content comment-content">
            <p>For those who are opposed to cyclists on the road, I believe nothing will appease them.  They drive aggressively and abusively around slow-moving cars, and I believe they will continue to drive aggressively and abusively around cyclists, licensed or not.</p>

<p>Moreover, I am concerned about the chilling effect a licensing requirement would have on cycling.  The single thing that makes me feel safer on the road is other cyclists.  Would the number of cyclists dwindle if cycling becomes more of a hassle than it already is?</p>


